<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,474,1147]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,342,654,679]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">Recognition</emphasis>
. Large species of the 
<emphasis box="[590,880,654,678]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">P. pallidiventris-cursitans</emphasis>
group (body 3.0– 
<quantity box="[1082,1172,655,679]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
); occiput with 
<number box="[1340,1354,655,679]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of black verticals; antenna brown to black, postpedicel about twice longer than wide, stylus 
<number box="[1234,1268,690,715]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X longer than postpedicel; palpus brown, large, oval; mesonotum grey pollinose, with black bristles, 
<number box="[1257,1271,727,751]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" value="2.0">2</number>
notopleurals, katepisternum with polished black patch; legs yellow in ground-colour; mid tibia with long pointed apical spur; abdomen almost entirely shiny black.
</paragraph>
